1. It is open-source, therefore, free 
2. Use existing OpenSSH
3. No agent installation or updating
4. Python/yaml based
5. It runs playbooks parallelly on your nodes
6. Larget number of predifined modules for use 
7. You can add custom modules 
8. Can run ad hoc commands and playbooks(group of commands/actions)
9. Ansible is idompotent, which means if there is no change then Ansible won't apply it. 
